para_trans: Under Section 26 (2) and (3) of the Right to Information Act, 2005, financial approval for the printing of the poster is granted.
Reference - 1. Letter from Yashwantrao Chavan Development Administration Prabodhini, Pune No. CRTI - 1725/01 AIST RE (2) / 2025-26, dated 22.12.2025 letter 2. Government Decision No. January 21, 2026

The Government of Maharashtra has issued guidelines for printing and distribution of 20000 copies of the Marathi language guidelines of reasonable information required to use the Act under Section 26 (2) and 26 (3) of the Right to Information Act, 2005 at a cost of Rs. 12.79 This amounts to Rs. 2,55,800 - Reference No. Administrative approval has been granted under Section 2.

2. The Government of Maharashtra is approving the release of funds to the tune of Rs. 2,55,800 - (Rupees Two Lakhs Eight Hundred Only) to Yashwantrao Chavan Development Administration Prabodhini for printing guidelines under the Right to Information Act, 2005 BFGF Baril.

3. The Fund "Demand No. A-4, Accounts Heading 2070 - Other Administrative Services, 00-003 - Training - Scheme under State Schemes, (00) (09) Grant-in-Aid to Yashwantrao Chavan Development Administration Prabodhini, Pune for Training Fund of Right to Information Act (20700826) Dattamat, 31 - Grant-in-Aid "to be divided by the grant-in-aid sanctioned for the financial year 2025-26.
4. The said Government Decision, Finance Department, Informal Reference No. 50, Expenditure-4, D. The 29.01.2026 invoice is being issued with the consent received.
The government decision is available on the Government of Maharashtra website www-maharashtra.gov.in with the code 202602121405340007. The government decision is being digitally signed.
By order and in the name of the Governor of Maharashtra,
Digitally signed by HEMANT ANANT MAHAJAN Date: 2026.02.12 14:06:32 +05'30'
Deputy Secretary, Government of Maharashtra - 1. Director, Yashada, Pune (2 copies).
